At least 5 killed, 10 injured as Mangala Express derails near Nasik
NEW DELHI: At least five people have reportedly been killed and 10 others injured as several coaches of Mangala Express, travelling from New Delhi to Ernakulam, derailed near Nasik. Eye witnesses said at least 25 people are still feared trapped inside the mangled rail coaches. According to reports, the accident took place near Ghoti between Igatpuri and Nasik stations at about 6.00am. Rail route between Nasik and Mumbai has been blocked due to the derailment. Relief and rescue teams have rushed to the spot. The accident site is off-route which is hampering rescue efforts. The death toll is expected to rise as several coaches of the trains jumped tracks and have toppled over one another.More details awaited.